items.name: Krillin/クリリン - Dragon Ball | LoRA
items.description:
On my Quest of completing the the Z fighters, I bring Krillin. This is my first model with DadaptationAdam but to me is good and superior to my Adam8bit models, so I might remake some or all at some point, especially the older ones. Thanks to @LazyTrainer for the settings!

I have a kofi if you want to support my work. I also take commissions, so if you are interested on a training, check that out. I also have a Pixiv where I upload pics from testing and tease the things I'm working on! Or go to my wife's Pixiv, she has sexy pics of my LoRAs and WIPs.

About the LoRA, his appereance is kururin, black eyes, forehead mark, no nose, no sclera. The baldness and the forehead dots can be changed. As always, I'll leave examples in the gallery, I didn't inpaint anything so there's always room for improvement. All the pictures are made with weight 1.The source is mostly old, so I recommend using hires with 0.3-0.5 denoise depending on the model. If he has too many markings, you can inpaint them out, if he has less, I'm not sure they can be inpainted, so aim higher.

The outfits available are:

  • The start of Dragon Ball Z/Namek one: bald, orange dougi, orange pants, blue wristbands, blue sash, black flats, white socks, patch, sleeveless

  • The Saiyan armor (not perfect): bald, dark blue saiyan armor, black bodysuit, white gloves, white boots, pauldrons, faulds, biker shorts, short sleeves

  • The Android saga: bald, orange dougi, orange pants, blue wristbands, blue sash, black boots, dark blue shirt, patch, short sleeves

  • The Buu saga: medium hair, red t-shirt, light brown sweatpants, white ribbon, black sneakers, white wristbands - I recommend having forehead mark on negative here.

The Super hair was trained with short hair, alternate hairstyleBut, as it didn't stick that much. I was generating pictures and noticed that on some angles SD get confused with the eye positioning, I'll address that, closing eyes and the saiyan armor in a future version. Also, there's a lot of bleeding between outfits, if someone knows how I can prevent this better, I'm all eyes.

That's it! Leave reviews, funny pictures, etc. They really help to stay motivated.

items.name: Macro Hentai Diffusion
items.description:
This model generates big anime girls sitting on top of or hanging over cities and landscapes. It's fine-tuned for NSFW images and has a large NSFW preference.

This model was trained on 150 mostly NSFW images using Dreambooth and then merged with the "Giantess | Concept" LoRA from @LeonTalon which further refined the results.

Recommended settings for good results:

Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

Sampling steps: 30 steps

height and width: 512x512

CFG Scale: 7

Clip skip: 1

Further fine-tuning might give better results depending on your preferences

Higher resolution images (highly recommended if your PC can handle it!):

Hires. fix: enabled (scaling from 512x512 to 1024x1024)

Upscaler: Latent (bicubic)

Upscale by: 2

Denoising strength: 0.65

Hires steps: 0

I didn't do allot of experimenting with this other settings will probably give better results

Recommended networks for better results:

Easy Negative

negative prompt: easynegative

Very Bad Image Negative

negative prompt: verybadimagenegative_v1.3

Combining with other Lora's should be possible but requires tinkering with the Lora strength value and can have varied results

Recommended prompt use this as a starting off point or if you want to generate similar results to me:

prompt: high res, best quality, 1girl, macro, giantess, city, full body, breasts, breasts apart, nipples, areolae, large breasts, nude, public nudity, exhibitionism, solo, uncensored

negative prompt: easynegative, verybadimagenegative_v1.3, low quality, low res, blurry, cropped, censored, censor_bar, safety panties, safety knickers, mosaic, watermark, artist name, username, signature, furry, bad anatomy, multiple breasts, extra limb, bad hands, missing fingers

items.name: Amethyst
items.description:
What is Amethyst?

Amethyst is an anime-cg style art for illustrations, manga, comics, and more. I personally use this model for my works, which is well suited on one of my styles. Regarding text prompts, just be versatile and let your imagination flow.  And, just like most models it also has few issues with the hands, which can be easily mitigated with this model's inpainting (download separately) or some embeddings. (I still have other models, for some specific arts, yet to be released. Your support will go a long way, and a cup of coffee will keep me awake for many nights. Thank you in advance!)

This version of Amethyst does not include a VAE because the goal is for art versatility, wherein, you can use any VAE you like to produce unique aesthetics. Below are the recommended VAEs that you can use with this model to tweak a unique output.

Popular Variable Auto Encoder (VAE)

kl-f8-anime2 VAE (for anime)

anything VAE aka orangemix VAE (for anime)

blessed VAE (for anime)

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realism)

Sample images above were created with simple text prompts around default settings. More detailed prompts will produce much better results. As for text prompts, just let your imagination flow. One thing to take note, adding keywords like realistic, realism, photorealism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, hyper realistic etc. will make the image more real, and not including any word with real on them will make it look anime-ish.

Settings:

Sampling Method: Euler (realistic) or Euler A (anime)

Sampling Steps: 20 to 30

Resolution: 512x512, 512x768, 768x512

CFG Scale: 4 to 7

Popular Embeddings Used

Easy Negative

Deep Negative

Bad artist Negative embedding

veryBadImageNegative

bad_prompt Negative Embedding

negative_hand Negative Embedding

EnvyBetterHands LoCon

Detail Tweaker LoRA

SXZ Vivid Darkness

Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix

Limitations:

Do use this model within the boundaries of legalities; do not use it to harm people and entities, or any illegal matters. Using this model means that you alone is responsible for any forms of consequences good or bad, and the author has no liabilities. We all know that AI models can produce both safe and unsafe images for work, so be very responsible.  For all other matters do read the CreativeML-OpenRail-M license Other than that, enjoy using this model and I hope this will help you in your endeavours as an artist.

Support:

First of all, thank you for patronizing this model; it means my efforts didn't go to waste. My goal is to produce more free tools not just for myself and my work, but for others too. Your generosity will go more than a mile. Also, as an artist, writer, programmer, and overall freelancer, I accept commission job. Thank you so much for your support!

items.name: Arnold Schwarzenegger (Total Recall/90s Era) - HQ Dreambooth Trained
items.description:
High Quality Dreambooth (JP's repo) trained checkpoint of Arnold using HD film stills from the movies "Predator" & "Total Recall".

There are a couple LORAs of Arnold on Civitai, but imho for likeness this checkpoint will far out perform the Lora models. I'm going to stick w/ high quality checkpoints for people unless my attempts to extract to Lora are only marginally inferior. It's pretty easy to extract a Lora from these checkpoints on your own using the "Supermerger" extension for A1111. If you do make a Lora from this checkpoint (IE: if it works better w/ your workflow) please just keep it for personal use and don't share it out that way.

Use Hi-Res fix with a denoise strength in the .2 range for best results

Please post any images you created with this model that you enjoy - It's motivating to see people digging models

Trained locally w/ a 4090 using Joe Penna's Dreambooth repo (requires 24gb VRAM and in my experience out performs the extensions/etc).

Regarding the samples: I like to use controlnet w/ random movie still shots to put a model somewhere in frame or w/o something interesting going on. I'll usually grab some stills from Bing Images, or places like Shotdeck, throw them in a folder, and batch run them w/ either Canny (ending slider set 50 or below), or the Openpose model set a little below 100%. Due to this, some of the sample images won't be reproducible if you use the information Civitai breaks out. Also a few of the sample images have the original filename before I renamed the file to upload here - same exact thing.

items.name: st-AI-le [ARCHIVED]
items.description:
THIS MODEL HAS BEEN ARCHIVED AS IT IS HEAVILY OUTDATED AND BAD!

Huggingface link: https://huggingface.co/ai-characters/st-AI-le

  • Multiple characters

  • Many styles

  • One model

st-AI-le by AI_Characters

If you like what I do feel free to support me on KoFi so that I can offset some of my training costs! https://ko-fi.com/aicharacters

A comprehensive account of my VastAI expenditures can be found here: https://imgur.com/a/nFbyUwh

st-AI-le is an all-in-one model incorporating multiple popular characters and distinct styles within a single ckpt. It was trained using a 512 resolution on the base StableDiffusion 1.5 model, without incorporating merges of any kind. It is thus wholly trained "from scratch" so to speak.

Formerly known as "Char", st-AI-le is basically a whole new model. I spent 6 months and around 4400€ generating hundreds of test models with different hyperparameters and datasets to arrive at this moment in time.

st-AI-le is designed to be able to generate multiple very distinct styles and characters as true to their likeness as possible, while still being diverse and flexible in its output, and offering the ability to transfer those characters into other styles. st-AI-le is by no means perfect. It has its issues. It does not always generate the most diverse output, it has its own biases, it can be incoherent at times, and sometimes it fails to understand a prompt correctly. However, by my own opinion it is currently one of the models with the highest amount of different styles and characters available within a single ckpt, without merging multiple models together, while also still offering good likeness, diversity, flexibility, and lack of bias.

This model also offers concepts not seen in any other model yet, namely a person transforming into an animal ("morphing") and giant/miniature people. Both these concepts however are highly experimental right now and likely will only produce bad output, or at the very least be very dependent on the prompt/style used.

I will continue to improve st-AI-le moving forward.

Recommended settings for interference

These are my recommended settings for quick high quality results. These are also the settings on which I tested the model. I cannot guarantee that settings other than these - or textual inversions/loras/negative prompts for that matter - will work well or at all with my model, as I have not tested them.

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 35

  • CFG: 7

  • Resolution: 512x512 + using high-res fix to 1024x1024 with a denoising strength of 0.4

  • Textual Inversion/lora: none

  • Negative prompt: instagram, pastel, dada, zombie, ugly, surreal, text, watermark, abstract, old, fat, jpeg, black and white, vintage, amateur, film grain, evil, damaged, concept, unfinished, model, cover, clay, figure, toy, pixelated, bad, inexperienced, illogical, random, oversaturated, overexposed, rough, fake, unrealistic, sloppy, artificial, low budget, unprofessional, cropped, out of frame, low-quality, poorly drawn, deformed, bad proportions, malformed, imperfect, unnatural, extra, rushed, weird

For general directions on how to best prompt the model, see the samples.

I also highly recommend using at least ControlNet-OpenPose with this model to remove any potential anatomy incoherences!

In case you generate some beautiful artwork using my model, feel free to tag me with it on Twitter and/or Instagram!

https://www.instagram.com/ai_characters/

https://twitter.com/ai_characters/

Trained tags

These are the styles, characters, and concepts, with which this model was trained. Thus they exhibit a different behaviour within my model than they do in the base vanilla 1.5 StableDiffusion model. To prompt a certain style or character or concept, use these tags.

Artstyles

A LoRA trained on images from the artist Jellcaps (as the name implies). I had a dataset of ~100 images and I trained it using DAdaptation. The model can often have negative effects to anatomy, so you may want to reduce the weight of it from 1.

items.name: A1
items.description:
A1 - Anime Sauce Model Mix

This is probably gonna be my final public merge, I've covered about all I wanted to with models by now! Thanks for all the support along the way.

This model was specifically designed to include as many concepts as humanly possible to allow HEAVY lora use. Almost any lora you can throw at A1 should work. Model also will do hardcore but that's not really my jam, so I'll leave that to you guys to figure out!

HIGHLY recommend using:

  • adetailer extension - INVALUABLE for this kind of thing

  • https://civitai.com/models/22354/clearvae for the VAE, others will work but this one was what I stress tested this model with

  • UniPC / Euler a / DDIM for the sampler

All the image examples were made with wildcards for loras, which means it was randomly pulling loras to slap into the images (they should hopefully get tagged in the model info!), then I grabbed a swathe of them to use at random.

Special Thanks:

https://civitai.com/user/konyconi/

https://civitai.com/user/PettankoPaizuri/images

This is a Lyc.... No.

These are 2 separate LoRA's. Why? Even on Lycoris was some bleeding. I will retry it later on, but currently exhausted with this one, because it was retrained 6 times.

items.name: Sun Shang Xiang/孫尚香 - Dynasty Warriors 8 (w/ Cheongsam) | LoRA
items.description:
I was already working on this and @irrel released her today too, so I'm emphasizing that I trained the cheongsam (china dress for NAI).

I have a kofi if you want to support my work. I also take commissions, so if you are interested on a training, check that out. I also have a Pixiv where I upload pics from testing and tease the things I'm working on! Or go to my wife's Pixiv, she has sexy pics of my LoRAs and WIPs.

About the LoRA, her appereance is sunshangxiang, brown hair, green eyes, short hair, swept bangs. As always, I'll leave examples in the gallery, I didn't inpaint anything so there's always room for improvement. All the pictures are made with weight 1, except when I needed to change the colors of the clothes where I went to 0.9. Use realisticas negative as a bit of cosplay was used.

The outfits available are:

  • The standard one, that can be recolored: chinese clothes, red jacket, white shirt, red skirt, red knee boots, white short shorts, shorts under skirt, brown belt, red mini crown, red wrist cuffs, puffy short sleeves

  • The cheongsam: red china dress, side slit, red shoes The length of the dress can be adjusted with prompts, like short dress

You can use the accessories of the first outfit on the second. The red jacket is overfit, so it will try to appear on the dress from time to time, just reroll if that happens.

That's it! Leave reviews, funny pictures, etc. They really help to stay motivated.

This LoRA was trained on about 1500 images of Caucasian (probably Eastern European) lingerie models on various Chinese lingerie shops on sites like TMall, Alibaba, JD, etc. The model was trained on a hybrid of both Danbooru and conventional labels. I've included all of the conventional labels in a separate Wildcards file which you can use in, say, the Dynamic Prompts addon to generate images that are very similar to the training images.

This model was trained on SD1.5 as the base although it should work with many other 1.5 base models.

Note: to help with your prompting, please download the corresponding wildcards file for the Dynamic Prompts addon and have it pick a random prompt among 1500+ used to train the model by using __supercutelingerie__

items.name: Lindsey Stirling
items.description:
Lindsey Stirling (born September 21, 1986) is an American violinist, songwriter, and dancer.[ She presents choreographed violin performances, in live and music videos found on her official YouTube channel, which she created in 2007.

Stirling performs a variety of music styles, from classical to pop and rock to electronic dance music. Aside from original work, her discography contains covers of songs by other musicians and various soundtracks. Her music video "Crystallize" finished as the eighth-most watched video of 2012 on YouTube, and her cover version of "Radioactive" with Pentatonix won Response of the Year in the first YouTube Music Awards in 2013.[10] Stirling achieved one million singles sold worldwide by August 2014. As of May 10, 2023, her Lindseystomp YouTube channel exceeded 13 million subscribers and over 3 billion total views.

Stirling has been named in Forbes magazine's 30 Under 30 In Music: The Class Of 2015. Forbes notes her quarter-finalist position on America's Got Talent season five in 2010, a No. 2 position on the Billboard 200 for her second album Shatter Me in 2014, and her 11 million subscribers on YouTube.

Stirling's eponymous debut album was a commercial success in Europe, selling 200,000 copies in Germany, winning a platinum certification; three additional certifications were given by Austria, Switzerland and Poland. The album was nominated for the 2014 Billboard Music Awards for Top Dance/Electronic Albums. Stirling's second album Shatter Me won Top Dance/Electronic Album at the 2015 Billboard Music Awards.

Trained on 1.5 Base Model but examples are from Realistic Vision

Please drop me a comment/suggestion/criticism/recommendations for new models

items.name: Quasarcake
items.description:
Style LoRA trained on Quasarcake's style. Should work on most models with an anime bias, but the effect will be strongest on Anylora. I recommend pairing it with epi_noiseoffset LoRA to strengthen the contrast, and blessed vae for the same reason.

Recommended settings are as follows. If you're on Automatic WebUI, you can paste it in and save it as a preset style so you don't have to navigate as many tags.

Positive prompt:

mksks style, {prompt}, (masterpiece, best quality, high quality), <lora:Quasarcake768:0.8>, <lora:epi_noiseoffset2:1.5>

Negative prompt:

(worst quality, low quality, normal quality), (colored sclera:1.3), {prompt}

Generation parameters:

  • LoRA Weight: You can technically go up to 1.0 weight, but 0.8 is where you get the best balance imo.

  • Config: 7.5

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Sampler: Any, but all of the examples are DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Width/Height: Since the model is trained on a 768x768 dataset, it can handle higher resolutions pretty well, and lower resolutions tend to come out more "zoomed" than normal because of it (sometimes works out in your favor). All the examples except one are generated at 512x640.

  • Highres fix?: It's fairly stable, so you can get away with using latent if you like most of the time. Either Latent upscaler <=2x and <=0.6 denoising if it's single subject, or R-ESRGAN 4x with <=0.75.

  • Adetailer: The original style is kinda sketch-like around the eyes, which SD does not like. In the end, that results in blurry eyelashes. I can recommend running with Adetailer, if you find that to be an issue. This is especially useful if you're generating at lower resolutions due to VRAM restrictions.

items.name: Audrey Kawasaki Style
items.description:
Audrey Kawasaki is a contemporary American artist known for her distinctive style of combining elements of manga, Art Nouveau, and surrealism.

Her style can be described as delicate, ethereal, and introspective. Kawasaki's artwork often features young female subjects with hauntingly beautiful, wide-eyed expressions, often surrounded by elements of nature or symbolic imagery.

She predominantly works with mixed media, combining oil painting with graphite and other materials, which creates a unique and layered visual texture.

Kawasaki's compositions exude a sense of mystery, vulnerability, and emotional depth. Her use of soft, muted colors and subtle gradients adds a dreamlike quality to her pieces.

The subjects in Kawasaki's art often convey a sense of introspection, exploring themes of femininity, identity, and the complexities of human emotions.

Her art has gained significant popularity and has been exhibited in galleries worldwide. Audrey Kawasaki's captivating and evocative artwork continues to captivate viewers, inviting them into a world of beauty, introspection, and subtle symbolism.

items.name: Ben Aronson Style
items.description:
Ben Aronson is an American contemporary painter known for his urban landscapes and cityscapes.

His style can be described as vibrant, energetic, and expressive. Aronson's paintings often depict bustling city streets, capturing the energy and movement of urban life. He has a keen eye for capturing the interplay of light and shadow, using bold brushstrokes and a rich color palette to bring his subjects to life.

Aronson's work reflects his fascination with the built environment and the way people interact within it. He often focuses on capturing the atmosphere and mood of a scene, whether it be a crowded street corner, a bustling market, or a quiet café. His paintings have a sense of immediacy and a cinematic quality that draws viewers into the urban landscapes he portrays.

In addition to his urban scenes, Aronson also explores other subjects such as interiors, still lifes, and landscapes. However, it is his ability to capture the dynamism and vibrancy of city life that has garnered him recognition and acclaim.

Ben Aronson's art is celebrated for its masterful use of color, brushwork, and composition, capturing the essence of contemporary urban environments in a captivating and visually engaging way.
